<span id="freeTextContainer4493318717167010194">Also a well done movie, but if you saw that first do NOT let it stop you from reading the book. It&apos;s fantastic. I don&apos;t know anything about the Japanese culture, but I hope he didn&apos;t get much wrong, because he makes me feel like I do. The in-depth look at the culture &amp; times is very well done. There is plenty of action, romance &amp; suspense.<br/><br/>I was totally sucked into the culture, the restrictions of the society &amp; their ideas of honor, just as our hero was. Thankfully, I could emerge from the book. </span>
  <span id="freeText4493318717167010194" style="display:none">Also a well done movie, but if you saw that first do NOT let it stop you from reading the book. It's fantastic. I don't know anything about the Japanese culture, but I hope he didn't get much wrong, because he makes me feel like I do. The in-depth look at the culture &amp; times is very well done. There is plenty of action, romance &amp; suspense.<br /><br />I was totally sucked into the culture, the restrictions of the society &amp; their ideas of honor, just as our hero was. Thankfully, I could emerge from the book. From my perspective as a middle class American, the culture is horrifyingly restrictive. Still it was a great read. If you liked this, you'll love <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/42933.Tai_Pan__Asian_Saga___2_" title="Tai-Pan (Asian Saga, #2) by James Clavell" rel="nofollow noopener">Tai-Pan</a>.</span>
